    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Confessions of a Lonely Atheist</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Joe Todaro letter on Natalie Angier's Jan 14 article deplores organized religion</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I was pleased to read Angier's article. But she gives organized religion a free pass. As a cultural construct, it has a great deal to answer for -- from the carnage of the Crusades to the unending bloodletting in the Middle East to the zealotry of Christian Scientists who would deny their children medical care. If this is the moral behavior that is ''inextricably linked'' to religion, I'll take my chances in a universe governed by quarks and black holes.</p>
        <p>Joe Todaro  San Francisco</p>
      </block>
